 of perfectness no matter what”.</p><p> “People around me always tell me that I sounded amazing during my solo performances, but I never believe their words. I&#39;ve never once felt satisfied,” the MAMAMOO member added. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="(ENG)&#x1f484;7년만에 만난 마마핑크, 추억토크하다 눈물지은 사연..&#x1f62d;  | 아이돌보미 EP4" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0A9ib95MraE?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p></p><p> Wheein&#39;s appearance on Bomi&#39;s talk show comes shortly after she released her first full-length album &#39;In The Mood&#39; last week, led by its title track of the same name.</p><p> It is her third body of work as a soloist, following two her 2021 mini-album &#39;Redd&#39; and 2022 released &#39;WHEE&#39;. &#39;In The Mood&#39; contains 11 new tracks, one of which feature MAMAMOO bandmate <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/hwasa">Hwasa</a> . Watch the music video <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mamamoos-wheein-in-the-mood-video-3513713">here</a> .</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/mamamoo-wheein-nervous-on-stage-performing-solo-3518523">MAMAMOO&#39;s Wheein says she had “never been nervous on stage” until she went solo</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
